> I can only fprintf the state.url in decimal so it does contain something (In decimal 142924196)~

That doesn't make any sense to me. Are you using the %s format? `fprintf(stderr, "data->state.url: %s\n", data->state.url);`

> and it leaves via
> result = parseurlandfillconn(data, conn);
> if(result){
> goto out;
> }

`if(result)` is shorthand for `result != CURLE_OK` which means that the function failed. I don't know in what case that curl_url_set would be called again. Turn on verbose mode `-v`.

On my Windows machine I see 3 calls to curl_url_set for `curl google.com`. The first call is to check if the URL is for IPFS. The second call is the parseurlandfill call. The third call is after the transfer to parse the Location URL, as I suspected.
